OL,3,CPrincess of Wales praised for telling
OL,4,Cher children of cancer diagnosis
OL,6,FWhen children are not told about what
OL,7,Fis happening they can reach their own
OL,8,Fconclusions and mistakenly feel they
OL,9,Fare "in some way responsible or to
OL,10,Fblame", Prof Dalton said.
OL,12,FShe continued: "Despite adults'
OL,13,Funderstandable desire to protect
OL,14,Fchildren from upsetting or worrying
OL,15,Fnews, it is important to talk honestly
OL,16,Fto children and young people.
OL,18,F"Even very young children notice when
OL,19,Fthe adults around them are more
OL,20,Fstressed or start taking telephone
OL,21,Fcalls behind closed doors.
